      "id": 17,
      "question": "How does equals() and hashCode() affect HashMap?",
      "section": "Intermediate Level",
      "difficulty": "Medium",
      "tags": [
        "hashcode",
        "equals"
      ],
      "title": "How does equals() and hashCode() affect HashMap?",
      "sections": [
        {
          "type": "bullet",
          "heading": "Introduction",
          "items": [
            "hashCode() is used to decide the bucket index where the key is stored.",
            "equals() is used to identify the exact key within that bucket.",
            "When inserting (put):",
            "HashMap first checks hashCode()",
            "If hash matches, it then checks equals()",
            "If equals() returns true, the value is replaced",
            "When retrieving (get):",
            "Same hashCode() finds the bucket",
            "equals() finds the matching key",
            "If *hashCode()8 is not overridden properly:",
            "Keys may go to wrong buckets → poor performance",
            "If equals() is not overridden:",
            "Duplicate keys may be stored → data inconsistency",
            "Contract rule:",
            "If equals() is true, hashCode() must be same"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "heading": "Introduction",
          "content": "In short: hashCode() decides where the key goes, equals() decides which key it is."
        }
      ],
      "askedIn": [
        "Google",
        "Amazon"
      ],
      "expectedReadTime": "1 min"
